# TypeScript Style Guide

## Typing

- Strict typing everywhere, never use `any`, `unknown`, or `never`
- Export shared types from `src/types/index.ts`
- Use mapped and conditional types for advanced transformations
- Avoid type assertions with `as` or `!` unless absolutely necessary

## Naming

- Descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs: `isLoaded`, `hasError`, `canEdit`
- Constants for magic numbers and repeated values
- PascalCase for types/interfaces, camelCase for variables/functions

## Structure

- Imports always at top of file, no inline imports
- Functions max 50 lines, files max 400 lines — split if exceeds
- One module per file, related helpers can coexist

## Error handling

```typescript
// Use grammY error boundary for modules
bot.errorBoundary((err) => {
  console.error('Module error:', err);
}).use(moduleComposer);

// Wrap async service calls
try {
  const result = await someService();
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof SpecificError) {
    // handle specifically
  }
  throw error;
}
```

## Patterns

- grammY modules as `Composer<BotContext>` instances
- Prisma queries in service files, not in handlers
- Handlers delegate to services, services delegate to Prisma
- Use exhaustive switch for union types and enums
